Class InvokeMethodAction

java.lang.Object
  javax.swing.AbstractAction
      sudoku.si.InvokeMethodAction
All Implemented Interfaces:
ActionListener, Serializable, Cloneable, EventListener, Action
public class InvokeMethodAction
extends AbstractAction

Invoke-a-method action. Takes a method name and finds a VoidMethodInvokable somewhere up in its containment ancestry, and invokes it as its action. For this to work, the method named must have a void return type and take no arguments.

See Also:
VoidMethodInvokable, Serialized Form

actionPerformed

public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent ae)
Performs the action of invoking the method on the invokee. Does a lazy look for the invokee in the action's containment hierarchy and sets the method via "reflection" on the method name.

Parameters:
